  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: 2021.06.5-alpha\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Linux puc 5.8.0-59-generic #66~20.04.1-Ubuntu SMP Thu Jun 17 11:14:10 UTC 2021 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\n\r\nCommit hash : https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/commit/cc360ec65854d724873bb5907d239adff1b10559\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nGetting a transaction receipt returns an object with a `status` field, which should be formatted as `QUANTITY`.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nThe `status` field is formatted as a plain number.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n%  curl -s puc:8545 -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" --data '{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"id\": 1, \"method\": \"eth_getTransactionReceipt\", \"params\": [\"0xed0b0b132bd693ef34a72084f090df07c5c3a2ec019d76316da040d4222cdfb8\"]}' | jq -r .result.status\r\n\r\nThis prints \"0\", but should print \"0x0\".\r\n\r\n",
